.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-ZONES 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-zones \- zone definitions for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I zones
file defines the network security zones used by the firewall.  Every other
configuration file that references a zone name (interfaces, hosts, policy,
rules, …) must use zone names declared here.

The compiler reads this file during the IR-construction pass
.RB ( build_ir()
in
.IR compiler/ir.py ).
Each zone becomes a named chain group in the emitted
.I inet shorewall
nft table.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/zones
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.  Blank lines are ignored.  Columns are whitespace-separated.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ZONE	yes	Zone name; up to 10 alphanumeric characters
TYPE	yes	Zone type (see below)
OPTIONS	no	Zone options (comma-separated)
IN_OPTIONS	no	Interface ingress options for this zone
OUT_OPTIONS	no	Interface egress options for this zone
.TE

.SS Zone types
.TP
.B firewall
The firewall host itself.  There must be exactly one firewall zone (usually
named
.BR fw ).
.TP
.B ip
Dual-stack zone (IPv4 and IPv6).  Use this in merged
.I /etc/shorewall46
configs.
.TP
.B ipv4
IPv4-only zone.
.TP
.B ipv6
IPv6-only zone.
.TP
.B bport[6]
Bridge port zone.
.TP
.B ipsec[6]
IPSEC zone.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Minimal dual-stack setup:
.RS
.nf
#ZONE   TYPE    OPTIONS
fw      firewall
net     ip
loc     ip
dmz     ip
.fi
.RE
.PP
IPv4/IPv6 separate zones (legacy layout for
.I /etc/shorewall
+
.I /etc/shorewall6
):
.RS
.nf
fw      firewall
net     ipv4
loc     ipv4
.fi
.RE
.PP
Zone with IPSEC sub-zone:
.RS
.nf
fw      firewall
net     ip
loc     ip
vpn     ipsec
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-interfaces (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-policy (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5)

